rComments: Professor Chen made clear which content we needed to master, and what we were to be tested on so nothing was vague. He cared about his students and wanted us to succeed. If you are confused on something in lecture, let him know and he will go through the concept or an example. If you need help, ask or attend office hours. had some funny math jokes

Professor Chen's teaching is average to good, but his treatment of his students is top-tier. He actually respects us as people outside of the context of his class, which is more than I can say for most of the STEM profs I've had at UO. Would definitely take another class with him again if given the opprotunity.

He's hard to understand, nothing against English not being his first language, but you can tell he's having a hard time explaining the concepts. Easy concepts I already knew from data management class in high school were made confusing when explained in his lectures. Class could be 10x easier, just not with this professor.
